<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5218] Fileinstall MemoryLeak / Performance degradation in WatcherScanner</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5218</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;WatcherScanner has a Watcher (called ScannerWatcher &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;) which will fill a set with all files that have been changed, so that it then can iterate over that.&lt;br/&gt;
however the set will never be cleaned, which leads to the problem that removed entries will be &quot;removed&quot; over and over again. ultimately bringing the system to a halt because it is busy removing stuff&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12950771">FELIX-5218</key>
            <summary>Fileinstall MemoryLeak / Performance degradation in WatcherScanner</summary>
