                            <comment id="15196992" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2016 08:14:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user CodingFabian opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/felix/pull/59&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/felix/pull/59&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5218&quot; title=&quot;Fileinstall MemoryLeak / Performance degradation in WatcherScanner&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-5218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-5218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fileinstall: Removed files should no longer be considere&#8230;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &#8230;d changed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This is probably a regression from adding the stable checksum mechanism. All removed files need to be removed from the &quot;changed&quot; hash set, otherwise they would be seen next iteration again and again be considered as removed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can merge this pull request into a Git repository by running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    $ git pull &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/CodingFabian/felix&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/CodingFabian/felix&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5218&quot; title=&quot;Fileinstall MemoryLeak / Performance degradation in WatcherScanner&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-5218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-5218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively you can review and apply these changes as the patch at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/felix/pull/59.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/felix/pull/59.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

